<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="501" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1050,1938]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1050,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Okada, 1960" authorityName="Okada" authorityYear="1960" box="[594,882,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis box="[594,608,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[627,703,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">magna</emphasis>
(Okada, 
<number box="[817,875,1050,1074]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="1960.0">1960</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[961,1025,1051,1074]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Japan</collectingCountry>
and central 
<collectingCountry box="[1177,1244,1050,1074]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">China</collectingCountry>
in the shape of paramere and the vertical process of gonopods without spines distally, but differs from it in having the surstylus triangularly protruded submedially (
<figureCitation box="[565,649,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[620,649,1122,1146]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the ventral bridge of aedeagus with distally bifurcated process (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,1158,1182]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="501" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1050,1938]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1194,1219]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Description.</emphasis>
Frons black above, brown below, with a few thin, sparse interfrontal setae. Pedicel and first flagellomere grayish yellow. Face brown, with yellowish white patches on lower corners. Clypeus white medially, black laterally. Thorax orange brown, with black patches and pollinose pattern. Scutellum orange yellow, with brown patch medially. Legs yellow, dark brown on fore- and midleg femora, with 
<number box="[1124,1138,1302,1326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="3.0">3</number>
dark rings on each tibia. Abdominal first to fourth tergites yellow; second tergite with 
<number box="[887,901,1338,1362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="2.0">2</number>
blackish patches each side (submedially and laterally); third and fourth tergites each with broad, medially slightly protruded, black band on posterior margin and 
<number box="[151,165,1410,1434]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="1.0">1</number>
yellow patch laterally each side; fifth and sixth tergites nearly entirely black; sixth tergite broadened at posterior corners of lateral margins, 
<number box="[457,492,1446,1470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times broader than its dorsomedian section (see 
<figureCitation box="[1051,1118,1446,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1702,1725]" captionTargetBox="[187,1395,742,1651]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,724,1679]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Phortica (Allophortica) chingolaensis Chen &amp; Máca, sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopods (gon), aedeagal median rod (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (lateral view) (all scale lines = 0.1 mm through this paper)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282315/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1104,1118,1446,1470]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1157,1356,1446,1471]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" refString="Chen, H. W., Toda, M. J., Lakim, M. B. &amp; Mohamed, M. B. (2007) The Phortica sensu stricto (Insecta: Diptera: Drosophilidae) from Malaysia. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 55, 23 - 41." type="journal article" year="2007">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[1224,1282,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[1298,1356,1446,1470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Male terminalia: Epandrium lacking pubescence anteroventrally, with 
<number box="[893,907,1483,1506]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="7.0">7</number>
setae on dorsal to posterolateral portion each side (
<figureCitation box="[211,291,1518,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[263,291,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus lacking pubescence, with 
<number box="[714,728,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="1.0">1</number>
very strong spine (
<figureCitation box="[943,1023,1518,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[995,1023,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Additional plate between cerci and tenth sternite lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[560,650,1554,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[619,650,1554,1578]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
), Posterolateral lobe of hypandrium lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1419,1554,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1419,1554,1578]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paramere devoid of pubescence and tooth but with 
<number box="[736,750,1590,1614]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="3.0">3</number>
sensilla apically (
<figureCitation box="[956,1038,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[1010,1038,1590,1614]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal membranous tube with minute spinules medially (
<figureCitation box="[448,532,1626,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,263,996,1019]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,208,975]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,975]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 25. Phortica (Phortica) monocaena Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia: 23. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); 24. tenth sternite and additional plate (frontal view); 25. hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282321/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
Fig. 
<number box="[500,532,1626,1650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
